#!/usr/bin/perl

use 5.010001;
use strict;
use warnings;

# VERSION


1;
# ABSTRACT: Riap client shell
# PODNAME: peri-sh

=head1 SYNOPSIS

Access the local Perl realm:

 % peri-sh
 riap> pwd
 /

 riap> cd spanel/api

 riap> ls
 pl:/spanel/api/crontab/
 pl:/spanel/api/disk_usage/
 pl:/spanel/api/plan/
 ...

 riap>

Access an API starting-point:

 % peri-sh https://cpanlists.org/api/
 riap>


=head1 DESCRIPTION

An experimental shell for L<Perinci::Access>. Commands and details might still
change in the future.


=head1 COMMANDS

=head2 cd

=head2 pwd

=head2 ls

=head2 info

=head2 call

=head2 request


